TITLE: Traders betting Fed will cut rates at least 4 times this year to bail out economy
SUMMARY: Data from the CME Group on Friday showed raised odds the federal funds rate will fall to 3.00% to 3.25%, down from 4.25% to 4.50% where it is currently.

TITLE: Trump says his administration will check Fort Knox 'to make sure the gold is there'
SUMMARY: A drive to audit Fort Knox has gained steam recently from comments by Elon Musk on X.

TITLE: Trump takes aim at 'wasteful' government spending by ordering end to penny production
SUMMARY: The president said in a Truth Social post that stopping the mint from coining new pennies is another way to reduce 'wasteful' government spending.

TITLE: Stocks making the biggest moves after hours: Amazon, Pinterest, Expedia and more
SUMMARY: These are the stocks posting the largest moves in extended trading.

TITLE: Wall Street's fear gauge — the VIX — saw second-biggest spike ever on Wednesday
SUMMARY: The CBOE Volatility Index (.VIX) surged 74% to close at 27.62, up from around 15 earlier in the day.
